Now that we know the bicycle travels a distance of 20 feet in exactly 60 seconds, we can find its speed in inches per second. To convert from feet per minute to inches per second, we first convert feet into inches: there are 12 inches in a foot. Then, since the bicycle travels 20 feet in 60 seconds, we can say that it travels 240 inches (20 * 12) in 60 seconds. Dividing this distance by the number of seconds gives us the bicycle's speed in inches per second:

speed in inches/second = (240 inches)/(60 seconds) = \boxed{40 inches/second}

The answer is: 40.
